        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 3:58PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Grafton, or near Hoosick Falls, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bennington, Hoosick Falls, Pownal, Stamford, Hoosick, Pittstown,
North Bennington, Valley Falls, Woodford, Old Bennington, Hoosick
Junction, Paper Mill Village, Sodom, Petersburg Junction, East
Hoosick, Babcock Lake, Johnsonville, East Buskirk, Eagle Bridge, and
Factory Hollow.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
